          "payload": {},
          "sequence": 75,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I have completed my fault localization analysis. Let me summarize my findings:\n\n## Fault Localization Summary\n\n**File**: `drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c`\n\n**Data Structure**: `iwl_dev_info_table` (static const array)\n\n**Issue**: The Intel Wireless-AC 9260 card (device ID 0x2526) is missing device information entries for three PCI subdevice IDs: **0x4010**, **0x4018**, and **0x401C** in the `iwl_dev_info_table`.\n\n**Root Cause**: When these subdevices are not found in `iwl_dev_info_table`, the driver falls back to the generic configuration `iwl9000_trans_cfg` from the catchall entry in `iwl_hw_card_ids`. This generic configuration does not provide the correct firmware settings for the Wireless-AC 9260, resulting in firmware loading failures.\n\n**Solution**: Add three new `IWL_DEV_INFO` entries to the `iwl_dev_info_table` for device 0x2526:\n- `IWL_DEV_INFO(0x2526, 0x4010, iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg, iwl9260_160_name)`\n- `IWL_DEV_INFO(0x2526, 0x4018, iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg, iwl9260_160_name)`\n- `IWL_DEV_INFO(0x2526, 0x401C, iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg, iwl9260_160_name)`\n\nThese entries follow the same pattern as existing 9260 160MHz entries with different prefixes (0x0, 0x6, 0x8, 0xA, 0xE).\n\n**Result written to**: `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json`",
